  "prompt": "Which is best mobile under 15000?",
  "response": "As of 2023, there are several good smartphones available under \u20b915,000 in India, offering a balance of performance, camera quality, and battery life. Here are some of the best options:\n\n### 1. **Realme Narzo 60x 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.72-inch Full HD+ display with 120Hz refresh rate\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 6100+ processor\n     - 50MP primary camera\n     - 5000mAh battery with 33W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** Smooth display, 5G support, good battery life.\n   - **Cons:** Average low-light camera performance.\n\n### 2. **Redmi 12 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.79-inch Full HD+ display with 90Hz refresh rate\n     - Snapdragon 4 Gen 2 processor\n     - 50MP dual camera setup\n     - 5000mAh battery with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** Large display, efficient performance, 5G support.\n   - **Cons:** Slower charging compared to competitors.\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy M14 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.6-inch Full HD+ display with 90Hz refresh rate\n     - Exynos 1330 processor\n     - 50MP triple camera setup\n     - 6000mAh battery with 25W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** Excellent battery life, 5G support, decent cameras.\n   - **Cons:** Mediocre performance in heavy tasks.\n\n### 4. **Infinix Zero 30 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.78-inch Full HD+ AMOLED display with 120Hz refresh rate\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 8020 processor\n     - 108MP primary camera\n     - 5000mAh battery with 68W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** Stunning display, fast charging, high-resolution camera.\n   - **Cons:** Slightly over budget, but often discounted.\n\n### 5. **Tecno Pova 5 Pro**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.78-inch Full HD+ display with 120Hz refresh rate\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 6080 processor\n     - 50MP dual camera setup\n     - 5000mAh battery with 68W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** High refresh rate display, fast charging, good performance.\n   - **Cons:** Average camera performance in low light.\n\n### 6. **Motorola G54 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.5-inch Full HD+ display with 120Hz refresh rate\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 7020 processor\n     - 50MP dual camera setup\n     - 5000mAh battery with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** Clean Android experience, smooth display, 5G support.\n   - **Cons:** Slower charging compared to others.\n\n### 7. **POCO M6 Pro 5G**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.79-inch Full HD+ display with 90Hz refresh rate\n     - MediaTek Dimensity 6100+ processor\n     - 50MP dual camera setup\n     - 5000mAh battery with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** Solid performance, 5G support, large display.\n   - **Cons:** Average camera performance.\n\n### 8. **Itel S23+**\n   - **Key Features:**\n     - 6.78-inch Full HD+ AMOLED display with 120Hz refresh rate\n     - Unisoc T616 processor\n     - 50MP primary camera\n     - 5000mAh battery with 18W fast charging\n   - **Pros:** AMOLED display, good battery life, premium design.\n   - **Cons:** Average performance for heavy tasks.\n\n### Conclusion:\nIf you prioritize **performance and display**, the **Realme Narzo 60x** or **Infinix Zero 30** are excellent choices. For **battery life**, the **Samsung Galaxy M14 5G** stands out. If you want a **clean Android experience**, the **Motorola G54 5G** is a solid option.\n\nAlways check for the latest offers and discounts, as prices may vary.",
